'''Hailee Steinfeld''' (born December 11, 1996)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MSfjCG4V2GM&t=372s|title=Hailee Steinfeld Answers the Web's Most Searched Questions|magazine=[[Wired (magazine)|Wired]]|via=[[YouTube]]|date=November 2019|access-date=November 30, 2021|archive-date=November 30, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211130090010/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MSfjCG4V2GM&t=372s|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="BackStage">{{cite news|url=https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/girl-grit-58360/|title=A Girl With 'Grit'|last=Riley|first=Jenelle|newspaper=[[Backstage (magazine)|Backstage]]|date=December 13, 2010|access-date=December 20, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101223065112/http://www.backstage.com/bso/news-and-features-features/a-girl-with-grit-1004134005.story|archive-date=December 23, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref> is an American actress and singer. She had her breakthrough with the [[western film]] ''[[True Grit (2010 film)|True Grit]]'' (2010), which earned her [[List of awards and nominations received by Hailee Steinfeld|various accolades]], including nominations for an [[Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress|Academy Award]] and a [[BAFTA Award for Best Actress in a Leading Role|BAFTA  Award]].

Steinfeld gained wider recognition for her roles in the [[Pitch Perfect (franchise)|''Pitch Perfect'' film series]] (2015–2017) and ''[[The Edge of Seventeen]]'' (2016), which earned her a [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress – Motion Picture Comedy or Musical|Golden Globe]] nomination. She also starred in ''[[Ender's Game (film)|Ender's Game]]'' (2013), ''[[Begin Again (film)|Begin Again]]'' (2013) and ''[[Bumblebee (film)|Bumblebee]]'' (2018). She voiced [[Gwen Stacy (Spider-Verse)|Gwen Stacy / Spider-Woman]] in ''[[Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse]]'' (2018) and [[Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse|its 2023 sequel]], and [[Vi (League of Legends)|Vi]] in the [[Netflix]] series ''[[Arcane (TV series)|Arcane]]'' (2021–2024). She portrayed [[Emily Dickinson]] in the [[Apple TV+]] series ''[[Dickinson (TV series)|Dickinson]]'' (2019–2021), and has portrayed [[Kate Bishop (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Kate Bishop]] in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] since 2021.

Steinfeld gained recognition in music after performing "[[Flashlight (Jessie J song)|Flashlight]]" in ''[[Pitch Perfect 2]]'' (2015), signing with [[Republic Records]] soon after and released her debut single, "[[Love Myself (Hailee Steinfeld song)|Love Myself]]", followed by her debut [[extended play|EP]] ''[[Haiz (EP)|Haiz]]'' (2015). She went on to release a series of successful singles, including "[[Starving (song)|Starving]]", "[[Most Girls (Hailee Steinfeld song)|Most Girls]]" and "[[Let Me Go (Hailee Steinfeld and Alesso song)|Let Me Go]]". In 2020, she released her second EP, ''[[Half Written Story]]''.

==Early life==
Steinfeld was born on December 11, 1996, in the [[Tarzana, Los Angeles|Tarzana]] neighborhood of [[Los Angeles|Los Angeles, California]], the younger of two children of Cheri (''[[Given name|née]]'' Domasin), an interior designer, and Peter Steinfeld, a personal trainer.<ref name="DailyNews">{{cite news|last=Strauss|first=Bob|title=Thousand Oaks teen Hailee Steinfeld earns nods for big role in 'True Grit'|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Daily News]]|date=December 18, 2010|url=http://www.dailynews.com/news/ci_16894415|access-date=January 7, 2

